---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ProbabilitySimulator from '../../../components/diagrams/ProbabilitySimulator.svelte';
---

<Layout title="Probability" lang="en" backHref="/explore-math/en/grade-8/" backLabel="← Grade 8">
	<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Probability</h1>
	<p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-8">Calculate chances and understand random experiments</p>

	<section class="prose max-w-none">
		<h2>Randomness and Probability</h2>
		<p>Probability = favorable outcomes ÷ possible outcomes. For a fair die: P(6) = 1/6 ≈ 16.7%.</p>

		<h3>🧪 Experiment: Law of Large Numbers</h3>
		<p>Roll many times! With few rolls everything is wild. With many, each number approaches the expected 16.7%.</p>
	</section>

	<ProbabilitySimulator client:visible />

	<section class="prose max-w-none mt-8">
		<h3>💡 Key Concepts</h3>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Equally likely outcomes:</strong> All results have the same probability</li>
			<li><strong>Tree diagrams:</strong> For multi-stage experiments (coin + die)</li>
			<li><strong>Path rules:</strong> Multiply along a path, add parallel paths</li>
			<li><strong>Complement:</strong> P(not A) = 1 − P(A)</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
</Layout>
